A recent outbreak of listeriosis has prompted recalls of contaminated meat products, including hot dogs and packaged meats.
The Agriculture Department is investigating the source of the bacteria, urging consumers to return suspect products.
No illnesses have been linked to the recalled items, but precautions are advised due to the potential health risks.
The recall highlights the need for stricter food safety measures and increased inspections to prevent future outbreaks.
Additionally, concerns have been raised about the safety of imported foods, emphasizing the importance of thorough cooking and proper food handling to reduce the risk of foodborne illnesses.
